-- South African Lender May Sell a 15% Stake to Nafcoc, Business Report Says
-- Renee Bonorchis
-- 2010-08-02T05:24:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/south-african-bank-may-sell-a-15-stake-to-nafcoc-business-report-says.html

          
          
             One of South Africa’s listed banks
may sell as much as a 15 percent stake to the National African
Federated Chamber of Commerce and Industry,  Business Report 
said, citing the chamber’s secretary general, Gilbert Mosena.  
 Nafcoc , as its known, has 1.8 billion rand ($247 million)
available for the purchase and is in advanced discussions with a
lender it did not identify, according to the Johannesburg-based
daily newspaper.  
